# TRACE / ME Top-20 Claims View v0.1

Date: 2026-06-16  
Status: compressed view of the Claims Ledger after Frankenstein integration; not replacement ledger; not validation.

## Purpose

The full Claims Ledger is growing. This file is the fast-readable top layer: the twenty claims most likely to matter to a new reader, critic, or external AI.

```trace
Top_20 :=
  compression
  + orientation
  not:
    full_ledger
    proof
    validation
```

## Top 20 Claims

| ID | Claim | Status | Why it matters |
|---|---|---|---|
| C01 | TRACE is strongest right now as diagnostic/design grammar, not validation. | known_status | Blocks overclaim. |
| C02 | A safeguard must bite before harm hardens. | core_operator | Core timing test. |
| C03 | K collapses where Witness, Record, Authority, Time, Enforcement, or Repair is zero. | core_operator | Correction is conjunctive. |
| C04 | Case legibility is not validation. | known_guard | Stops bootstrap inflation. |
| C05 | AI agreement is readability/drift signal, not proof. | known_guard | Stops review laundering. |
| C06 | Legality is not identical to legitimacy. | boundary_claim | Tubman / predatory-system branch. |
| C07 | When official correction is dangerous or captured, diagnosis must include exit route and external constraint. | patterned_operator | Exit-route branch. |
| C08 | Protective secrecy is bounded; it must not become permission for opacity. | known_guard | Tubman guard. |
| C09 | Care with teeth means restoring option-space under constraint, not sentiment alone. | patterned_operator | Samwise/Tubman care operator. |
| C10 | Operational free will can be modeled as recursive branch-selection under constraint. | hypothesis_operator | Groundhog operator. |
| C11 | Recursion and repeated feedback do not guarantee moral progress. | known_guard | Anti-romantic recursion. |
| C12 | A training loop must be judged by what policy it teaches, not only by whether it converges. | alignment_hypothesis | Groundhog to AI bridge. |
| C13 | The Mandelbrot analogy is useful only when rule, iteration, boundary, and outcome-class are explicit. | boundary_claim | Blocks decorative mysticism. |
| C14 | Creation or activation of consequential power creates duties beyond technical success. | patterned_operator | Frankenstein operator. |
| C15 | Created origin and disturbing appearance cannot by themselves erase a subject-claim. | boundary_claim | Frankenstein subject-boundary guard. |
| C16 | Abandonment by a creator can be active harm when it closes care, correction, and integration routes. | patterned_operator | Repair-debt claim. |
| C17 | Technical activation is not ethical completion. | known_guard | Life/death and deployment guard. |
| C18 | Concealment of creator-causal knowledge can collapse K by blocking public record and repair. | diagnostic_pattern | Frankenstein K-gate link. |
| C19 | AI alignment requires lifecycle stewardship, not merely initial capability control. | alignment_hypothesis | Frankenstein to AI bridge. |
| C20 | No candidate branch should enter the Diagnostic Kernel before pressure-testing. | known_guard | Prevents Kernel bloat. |

